HEADWORD: Ragweed
<hw>Rag"weed`</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧g"w⟦emac⟧d`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A common American composite weed (<spn>Ambrosia
artemisiaefolia</spn>) with finely divided leaves; hogweed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Great ragweed</b></col>, <cd>a coarse American herb
(<spn>Ambrosia trifida</spn>), with rough three-lobed opposite
leaves.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

